rComments: best math out there for mat1700. dgds exercises are the same as your midterm. and finals are the same as dgds and your midterms. very good prof

Prof is bad, he writes irrelevant stuff on the board and has no control over the class. TA was amazing! You only need to show up to DGD's in order to do well in this class. Only reason I loved this prof, is because ALL his exams reflect EXACTLY what's in the DGD's! So there's no surprises. This class is almost the same as calculus grade 12!!

He is very bad at teaching. You can't hear him, he writes irrelevant notes on the board and has no control at all over the classroom. One class he even left in the middle because everyone was talking. That's when I stopped going to class. His exams are very easy tho. Just make sure to go to the DGD and if you understand that you'll get an easy A.

This man just storms thru all the material. He has a mic on, but even with it ON, no one can hear him speak, so he's basically mumbling for an hour and a half to himself while writing a ton of material on the board that no one understands. DGD's are useful though

François est un excellent prof de math! Il suit le recueil de notes, donc il est possible de suivre le cours dans le recueil et non prendre des notes interminables.  Les examens reflètent exactement la matière pratiquée dans les DGD.
